trans-unit.source: Represents a single user interface (UI) entity managed by an <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Adorner" />.
trans-unit.target: Representa una entidad de interfaz de usuario (IU) única administrada por <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Adorner" />.

trans-unit.source: The sole purpose of a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> is to paint and hit test.
trans-unit.target: El único propósito de un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> es pintar y realizar pruebas de posicionamiento.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> does not have a window handle (HWND), as it is rendered on the adorner window control of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService>.
trans-unit.target: A <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> no tiene un identificador de ventana (HWND), como se representa en el control de la ventana de adorno de la <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService>.

trans-unit.source: Each <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> can have a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Behavior> associated with it.
trans-unit.target: Cada <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> puede tener un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Behavior> asociados a él.

trans-unit.source: A successfully hit-tested <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> has the opportunity to push a new or different <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Behavior> onto the behavior stack of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService>.
trans-unit.target: Una prueba de detección correctamente <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> tiene la oportunidad para insertar un nuevo o diferente <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Behavior> en la pila de comportamiento de la <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService>.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [Behavior Service Overview](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7c60cc41-4324-46b5-b444-b39eda7cb33f).
trans-unit.target: Para obtener más información, consulte [Introducción al servicio de comportamiento](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7c60cc41-4324-46b5-b444-b39eda7cb33f).

trans-unit.target: Proporciona la lógica de la prueba de detección.

trans-unit.source: A <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Cursor" /> if the <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph" /> is associated with <paramref name="p" />; otherwise, <see langword="null" />.
trans-unit.target: <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Cursor" /> si el <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph" /> está asociado a <paramref name="p" />; de lo contrario, es <see langword="null" />.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph.GetHitTest%2A> method is an `abstract` method that forces <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> implementations to provide hit test logic.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph.GetHitTest%2A> método es un `abstract` método que fuerza <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> implementaciones para proporcionar lógica de prueba de posicionamiento.

trans-unit.source: Given any point, if the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> has decided to be involved with that location, it will need to return a valid <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Cursor>.
trans-unit.target: Cualquier momento dado, si la <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> ha decidido implicada en una que ubicación, deberá devolver válido <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Cursor>.

trans-unit.source: Otherwise, returning `null` will cause the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService> to ignore the location.
trans-unit.target: En caso contrario, devuelve `null` hará que el <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService> para pasar por alto la ubicación.
